end down (as an elephant to strike with his tusks); <span class='sdata'>vaprakrīḍāpariṇatagajaprekṣaṇīyaṃ dadarśa</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Me. 2</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>viṣke nāgaḥ</span> <span class='sdata'>paryaṇaṃsīt sva eva</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Śi. 18. 27.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>2</strong> To bend or bow down, be inclined; <span class='sdata'>lajjāpariṇataiḥ (vadanakamalaiḥ)</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Bh. 1. 4.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>3</strong> To be changed or transformed into, assume the form of (with <span>instr.</span>); <span class='sdata'>latābhāvena pariṇatamasyā rūpaṃ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>V. 4</span>&nbsp;; <span class='ls' title='V.'>4. 28</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>kṣīraṃ jalaṃ vā svayameva dadhihimabhāvena</span> <span class='sdata'>pariṇamate</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ś. B.</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Me. 45.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>4</strong> To result, happen; <span class='sdata'>sarvaṃ viparītaṃ pariṇamati</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Mk. 1.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>5</strong> To be developed or matured, be ripe; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Me. 18</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ki. 5. 37</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>M. 3. 8</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Rs. 1. 26</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Mv. 1. 12</span>&nbsp;; see <span class='sdata'>pariṇata</span> below. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>6</strong> To be advanced (in age), grow old, be aged, decay; <span class='sdata'>pariṇataśaraccādrikāsu kṣapāsu</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Me. 110</span>&nbsp;; so <span class='sdata'>jarāpariṇata</span> &c. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>7</strong> To set, decline in the west (as the sun); <span class='sdata'>anena samayena</span> <span class='sdata'>pariṇato divasaḥ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>K. 47.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>8</strong> To be digested; <span class='sdata'>grastaṃ pariṇamecca yat</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Mb.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>9</strong> To be cooked or roasted; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Māl. 5. 17.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>10</strong> To elapse (as time). <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><i>— <span>Caus.</span></i> <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>1</strong> To make ripe, mature, develop, perfect. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>2</strong> To pass (as the night). <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>3</strong> To stoop, bend oneself down.","evidence":{"band":3,"band_label":"common -- recognise","rank_all":4657,"count_all":104,"first_era":"Vedic","genre":null,"example":{"sa":"pariṇata","ru":"мудрый","work":"02_ramayana-ayodhyakanda","passage":"43.16","kind":"translation","source":"corpus_lexicon.jsonl (pwg_ru Phase 4, SanskritLexicography/RussianTranslation)"},"badges":[{"field":"band","value":3,"label":"common -- recognise","source":"kosha frequency layer, rank_all (DCS archive.sqlite M9 via VisualDCS)"},{"field":"count_all","value":104,"label":"104 attestations in DCS","source":"DCS archive.sqlite M9 (VisualDCS)"},{"field":"first_era","value":"Vedic","label":"first attested: Vedic","source":"DCS archive.sqlite M9 (VisualDCS)"},{"field":"genre","value":null,"label":"genre sketch not derivable from current DCS extraction (only a chronological period vector is stored, no per-genre breakdown)","source":"n/a -- gap documented, not fabricated (see app/evidence.py)"}]}}]}